modules.description: This module provides type-safe routing operations for matching HTTP requests to handler functions using path and query parameter patterns. It works with HTTP methods, request paths, and query strings, converting them into typed OCaml values through combinators like `/`, `arg`, and `qint` for structured route composition. Typical use cases include building web APIs with precise parameter extraction (e.g., parsing user IDs from paths or boolean flags from queries) and creating nested route hierarchies with static and dynamic segments.
